he-aisle-siddharth-smiles-6578671%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russians%20Urged%20To%20Have%20Sex%20During%20Work%20Breaks%20Amid%20Declining%20Birth%20Rate%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20reportedly%20encouraged%20Russians%20to%20engage%20in%20intimate%20relations%20during%20lunch%20and%20coffee%20breaks%20at%20work%20to%20address%20the%20country's%20declining%20birth%20rate.%20The%20initiative%20comes%20as%20Russia's%20fertility%20rate%2C%20currently%20at%20about%201.5%20children%20per%20woman%2C%20falls%20significantly%20below%20the%202.1%20rate%20required%20to%20maintain%20a%20stable%20population%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2C%20noindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmetro.co.uk%2F2024%2F09%2F15%2Fvladimir-putin-demands-russians-sex-work-fall-birth-rate-21608541%2F%5C%22%3EMetro%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%20Additionally%2C%20over%20a%20million%2C%20primarily%20younger%20Russians%2C%20have%20left%20the%20country%20amid%20the%20ongoing%20war%20with%20Ukraine%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealth%20Minister%20Dr%20Yevgeny%20Shestopalov%20emphasised%20that%20being%20too%20busy%20at%20work%20is%20not%20a%20valid%20excuse%20for%20avoiding%20procreation.%20He%20suggested%20that%20people%20could%20take%20advantage%20of%20breaks%20to%20focus%20on%20expanding%20their%20families%2C%20noting%20that%20''life%20flies%20by%20too%20quickly.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20reporter%20asked%20him%20how%20people%20working%2012%20to%2014%20hours%20a%20day%20would%20find%20time%20to%20have%20children%2C%20he%20responded%20by%20suggesting%20they%20could%20use%20their%20break%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20Putin%20has%20insisted%2C%20''The%20preservation%20of%20the%20Russian%20people%20is%20our%20highest%20national%20priority.%20The%20fate%20of%20Russia....depends%20on%20how%20many%20of%20us%20there%20will%20be.%20It%20is%20a%20question%20of%20national%20importance.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Russia's%20birth%20rate%20has%20hit%20its%20lowest%20point%20since%201999%2C%20with%20the%20number%20of%20live%20births%20in%20June%20falling%20below%20100%2C000.%20This%20drastic%20drop%20has%20raised%20concerns%20in%20Moscow%20about%20a%20severe%20population%20decline.%20According%20to%20Rosstat%2C%20Russia's%20governmental%20statistics%20agency%2C%20the%20country%20has%20seen%20a%20significant%20decrease%20in%20births%2C%20with%2016%2C000%20fewer%20children%20born%20between%20January%20and%20June%202024%20compared%20to%20the%20same%20period%20last%20year%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.euronews.com%2F2024%2F09%2F10%2Frussias-birth-rate-drops-to-its-lowest-in-a-quarter-century-data-shows%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEuro%20News%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20decline%20is%20further%20exacerbated%20by%20an%2018%25%20increase%20in%20population%20decline%2C%20with%2049%2C000%20more%20deaths%20recorded%20in%202024%20than%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20likely%20due%20to%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin's%20efforts%20to%20boost%20Russia's%20declining%20birth%20rate%20have%20led%20to%20a%20series%20of%20measures%2C%20including%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFree%20fertility%20checks%3A%20Women%20in%20Moscow%2C%20aged%2018-40%2C%20are%20encouraged%20to%20undergo%20free%20fertility%20assessments%20to%20evaluate%20their%20%26quot%3Breproductive%20potential%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEmployer%20coercion%3A%20MP%20Tatyana%20Butskaya%20has%20proposed%20a%20plan%20to%20pressure%20employers%20into%20encouraging%20their%20female%20employees%20to%20have%20children.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIncentives%3A%C2%A0Chelyabinsk%20region%20is%20offering%C2%A08%2C500%20pounds%C2%A0to%20female%20students%20under%2024%20for%20their%20first%20child's%20birth%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERestricting%20abortion%3A%20Access%20to%20abortion%20across%20the%20country%20is%20being%20blocked%20as%20public%20figures%20and%20churchmen%20claim%20women's%20duty%20is%20to%20give%20birth%20and%20raise%20children.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDivorce%20fees%3A%C2%A0Fees%20for%20divorce%20have%20been%20increased%20to%20discourage%20separation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitician%20Anna%20Kuznetsova%20has%20also%20demanded%20women%20start%20giving%20birth%20at%20a%20young%20age.%20She%20said%3A%20''You%20should%20start%20giving%20birth%20at%2019-20%20years%20old.%20Then%2C%20statistically%2C%20the%20family%20will%20be%20able%20to%20have%20three%2C%20four%2C%20or%20more%20children.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20critics%20argue%20these%20policies%20undermine%20individual%20autonomy%2C%20particularly%20for%20women%2C%20and%20may%20have%20unintended%20consequences%20on%20Russia's%20social%20fabric.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726489560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fetden2mo_vladimir-putin_625x300_13_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussians-urged-to-have-sex-during-work-breaks-amid-countrys-declining-birth-rate-6578255%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20initiative%20comes%20as%20Russia's%20fertility%20rate%2C%20currently%20at%20about%201.5%20children%20per%20woman%2C%20falls%20significantly%20below%20the%202.1%20rate%20required%20to%20maintain%20a%20stable%20population.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Frussians-urged-to-have-sex-during-work-breaks-amid-countrys-declining-birth-rate-6578255%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Will%20Kejriwal's%20Brand%20of%20Victimhood%20Politics%20Work%20Again%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fw.ndtvimg.com%2Fsites%2F3%2F2019%2F10%2F04163431%2Farvind-kejriwal-banega-swasth-india.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20Arvind%20Kejriwal's%20surprise%20announcement%20on%20Sunday%20that%20he%20would%20resign%20as%20Delhi%20Chief%20Minister%20in%20two%20days%2C%20Delhi%20Government%20ministers%20and%20senior%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20leaders%20have%20been%20working%20overtime%20to%20reclaim%20the%20moral%20high%20ground%20and%20sympathy%20for%20their%20leader.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20they%20seem%20to%20be%20relying%20on%20the%20belief%20that%20public%20memory%20is%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20first%20public%20address%20after%20being%20released%20on%20bail%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court-following%20over%20five%20months%20in%20jail-Kejriwal%20argued%20that%20the%20Apex%20Court%20had%20granted%20him%20bail%20in%20the%20alleged%20cases%2C%20even%20though%20he%20was%20booked%20under%20the%20stringent%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA).%20He%20claimed%20that%20the%20Court%20had%20given%20him%20the%20best%20possible%20relief%20and%2C%20since%20the%20trial%20and%20final%20verdict%20on%20the%20alleged%20excise%20scam%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20prolonged%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20step%20down%20temporarily.%20He%20stated%20he%20would%20not%20occupy%20the%20chief%20minister's%20chair%20until%20people%20certify%20his%20%26quot%3Bhonesty%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20upcoming%20Delhi%20Assembly%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHaving%20A%20'Nightwatchman'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%20is%20scheduled%20to%20begin%20the%20electoral%20process%20in%20January%202025%2C%20but%20Kejriwal%20now%20wants%20the%20elections%20to%20be%20held%20in%20November.%20In%20either%20case%2C%20Kejriwal%20aims%20to%20have%20what%20is%20known%20in%20cricketing%20terms%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bnightwatchman%26quot%3B-someone%20to%20keep%20the%20position%20warm%20for%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20AAP%20leaders%20are%20working%20to%20convince%20the%20public%20that%20Kejriwal%20is%20making%20a%20significant%20sacrifice%20and%20stands%20firm%20on%20the%20moral%20front.%20Their%20main%20arguments%20are%20as%20follows%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKejriwal%20is%20the%20first%20politician%20to%20seek%20a%20certificate%20of%20honesty%20from%20the%20public%20in%20an%20election%3B%20voters%20should%20elect%20him%20if%20they%20believe%20he%20is%20honest.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKejriwal%20is%20the%20first%20politician%20to%20resign%20after%20coming%20out%20of%20jail%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bpeople's%20court%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20highest%20court%2C%20and%20they%20will%20decide%20whether%20he%20is%20honest%20while%20the%20legal%20system%20evaluates%20the%20merits%20of%20the%20charges%20brought%20by%20the%20ED%20and%20CBI.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKejriwal%20did%20not%20resign%20in%20the%20past%20six%20months%2C%20following%20his%20arrest%20on%20March%2021%2C%20because%20resigning%20would%20have%20set%20a%20precedent%20that%20could%20embolden%20the%20Modi%20government%20to%20imprison%20opposition%20chief%20ministers%20and%20break%20their%20parties.%20By%20not%20resigning%2C%20Kejriwal%20thwarted%20the%20BJP's%20plans.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20examine%20these%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20when%20Kejriwal%20says%20he%20will%20return%20as%20chief%20minister%20once%20the%20people%20give%20a%20mandate%20to%20AAP%2C%20he%20conveniently%20overlooks%20two%20crucial%20conditions%20imposed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3A%201)%20he%20cannot%20attend%20the%20Delhi%20Chief%20Minister's%20office%2C%20and%202)%20he%20cannot%20sign%20off%20on%20files.%20These%20conditions%20imply%20that%20he%20cannot%20hold%20Cabinet%20meetings%20or%20engage%20in%20policy-making%20or%20policy%20reviews.%20Such%20conditions%20suggest%20that%20even%20with%20new%20elections%2C%20Kejriwal%20would%20remain%20a%20dysfunctional%20chief%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20conditions%20differ%20from%20disqualification%20cases%20like%20Sonia%20Gandhi's%20office%20of%20profit%20case%2C%20where%20a%20politician%20is%20disqualified%20for%20a%20specific%20issue%20but%20may%20be%20re-elected%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKejriwal%20knew%20well%20that%2C%20according%20to%20the%20court%20order%2C%20he%20could%20have%20remained%20chief%20minister%20in%20title%20only%2C%20without%20the%20actual%20responsibilities%20of%20the%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoll%20Victory%20Isn't%20An%20Absolution%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20claim%20that%20a%20win%20in%20a%20fresh%20election%20would%20be%20a%20certificate%20of%20honesty%20from%20the%20people%20is%20dubious.%20For%20example%2C%20former%20Bihar%20Chief%20Minister%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%2C%20Om%20Prakash%20Chautala%2C%20and%20Sukh%20Ram%20were%20re-elected%20despite%20being%20convicted%20in%20court.%20Their%20victories%20did%20not%20necessarily%20validate%20their%20honesty.%20If%20re-election%20were%20a%20true%20indicator%20of%20honesty%2C%20it%20would%20imply%20that%20almost%20no%20politician%20in%20India%20is%20corrupt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKejriwal%20should%20have%20followed%20LK%20Advani's%20example%2C%20who%2C%20when%20charged%20in%20the%20Jain%20Hawala%20case%2C%20announced%20he%20would%20not%20seek%20public%20office%20until%20he%20cleared%20his%20name%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERunning%20The%20Government%20From%20Jail%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20the%20claim%20that%20Kejriwal%20is%20the%20first%20chief%20minister%20to%20resign%20after%20bail%20may%20make%20for%20good%20TV%20debates%20but%20is%20not%20grounded%20in%20historical%20context.%20It%20has%20been%20an%20unwritten%20norm%20for%20a%20chief%20minister%20facing%20imminent%20arrest%20to%20resign%20and%20transfer%20responsibilities.%20Examples%20include%20Lalu%20Yadav%20in%20Bihar%2C%20Uma%20Bharti%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Jayalalithaa%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20more%20recently%2C%20Hemant%20Soren%20in%20Jharkhand.%20However%2C%20Kejriwal%2C%20who%20presents%20himself%20as%20a%20crusader%20against%20corruption%2C%20chose%20not%20to%20resign%20and%20continued%20as%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20exploiting%20the%20legal%20ambiguities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20did%20not%20explicitly%20ask%20him%20to%20resign%2C%20as%20no%20such%20law%20exists%2C%20but%20their%20bail%20order%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20his%20position%20as%20chief%20minister%20was%20untenable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Kejriwal's%20arrest%20and%20subsequent%20judicial%20custody%2C%20AAP%20leaders%20claimed%20he%20could%20run%20the%20Delhi%20government%20from%20jail.%20Delhi's%20Cabinet%20Minister%20Atishi%20Marlena%20even%20held%20a%20press%20conference%20with%20a%20directive%20from%20Kejriwal%20regarding%20water%20and%20sewage%20issues.%20However%2C%20this%20claim%20was%20proven%20false%2C%20as%20Kejriwal%20could%20not%20effectively%20manage%20the%20government%20from%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFourth%2C%20any%20student%20of%20politics%20would%20understand%20that%20recent%20Supreme%20Court%20rulings%20on%20Article%20356%20and%20defection%20have%20made%20legal%20scrutiny%20rigorous.%20Additionally%2C%20destabilising%20a%20government%20is%20only%20feasible%20with%20a%20thin%20majority%20and%20significant%20internal%20party%20divisions.%20The%20AAP%20in%20Delhi%2C%20the%20Trinamool%20Congress%20government%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20and%20the%20DMK%20government%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20all%20have%20substantial%20majorities%2C%20making%20it%20nearly%20impossible%20for%20rival%20political%20formations%20to%20engineer%20defections%20and%20destabilise%20these%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Kejriwal%20thrives%20on%20victimhood%20politics%2C%20using%20it%20as%20a%20strategy%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20headlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Sanjay%20Singh%20is%20Contributing%20Editor%2C%20NDTV)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3